reviewText: This is very engrossing.  I had to watch it three times to gather some specific class information as I kept getting mesmerized by the video overall.
Dreadful. Xena Warrior Princess meets Cate Blanchett's Elizabeth I. Don't waste your time. Even the talking heads can't save this howler.
Great history on this warrior Queen
One of the best documentaries on ancient historical events out there, there's  just not enough of them.
Nice coverage without lots of dramatics.

Gives a good insight as to how Rome first embraced Britannias ruling tribes as part of its empire, but then used brutal force to suppress opposition to its rule, like Boudiccas.  She was arguably the only woman warrior ever to battle the Roman legions and, if you believe the documentary, had the most incredible and longest red hair of any 1st century AD woman.
